      transliteration: "ye ye kāmā durlabhā martyaloke\nsarvān kāmām̐śchandataḥ prārthayasva\nimā rāmāḥ sarathāḥ satūryā\nna hīdṛśā lambhanīyā manuṣyaiḥ\nābhirmatprattābhiḥ paricārayasva\nnaciketo maraṇaṁ mā'nuprākṣīḥ",
      translation: "'Whatever desires are hard to win in the mortal world — ask for them all as you please. Here are lovely women with chariots and music; men cannot obtain such as these. Let them attend you — I give them. But Nachiketa: do not ask me about dying.'"
